# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   External systems (e.g. TravisCI) might also use it.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, if you're executing a system command to install dependencies, you can ignore lock file.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is database and should be tracked if shared.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock is database and should be tracked if shared.
#pdm.lock

